cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper uses deep learning techniques to analyze eye-tracking data of subjects with probable Alzheimer's disease and healthy control subjects. This involves processing and analyzing natural language sentences, which suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of deep neural networks and sparse-autoencoders also suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE).
